 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>VtynofSaryrn</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I don't think most necros really come to realize the importance of Hit Points until they hit 44 or 49.  This being the case, having an unusually large hit point pool before then is probably not necessary.</P><P>This could be due to a number of things, including the fact that every other caster out there is screaming about INT all the time.  But also includes the fact that Pact of Shadow (44) and Lich (49) REALLY suck your Hit Points.  I know that once i saw how effective Pact could be, all i wanted was more Hit Points.. then when i learned how much STA can affect Hit Points beyond level 50, STA became very important to me also.</P><P>So basically, before level 44 your primary concern should be getting your INT up toward and above 200.  After 44 you should think about where you can swap out pure INT items for items that supply both INT and Hit Points, or INT and STA.  </P><P>Always remember that as a necromancer your Hit Points are going to be your bread and butter post 50. Good healers will not heal you when you are a little low on Hit Points b/c they know you can heal yourself.  When you are soloing, nobody can hear you scream when mobX breaks fear and snare at the same time and is beating you down while you frantically try to land a spell on it or FD.</P><P>Your Hit Points , most importantly, keep you alive.. AND they are your primary source of Mana Regeneration. Never forget.</P><P>Vtyn</P><P> </font></td>
